8.1

a

Which do you think is bigger \(\operatorname{Var}[y_{i,j} | \theta_i , \sigma^2]\) or \(\operatorname{Var}[y_{i,j} | \mu, \tau^2]\)?

후자는 그룹들간의 분산을 포함하므로 더 크다.

b

Do you think \(\operatorname{Cov}[y_{i_1, j} , y_{i_2,j} | \theta_j , \sigma^2]\) is negative or positive or zero?

Exchangeability에 의해서 Conditional independent

Do you think \(\operatorname{Cov}[y_{i_1, j} , y_{i_2,j} | \mu, \tau]\) is negative or positive or zero?

\(p(y_{i_2, j} | \mu, \tau) \neq p(y_{i_2, j} |y_{i_1, j} ,\mu, \tau)\)

그러므로 0이 아니라고 생각한다. posterior 분포는 sample에 다가가면서 결정되므로그러므로 양수라고 생각한다.

c

\(\operatorname{Var}[y_{i,j} | \theta_i , \sigma^2] = \sigma ^2\)

\(\operatorname{Var}[\bar y_{\cdot,j} | \theta_i , \sigma^2] = \frac{\sigma ^2}{n_j}\)

\(\operatorname{Cov}[y_{i_1, j}, y_{i_2, j}| \theta_j, \sigma^2] = 0 \quad \because \text{Exchangeability}\)

\(\begin{align}\operatorname{Var}[y_{ij} | \mu , \tau^2] &= \operatorname{Var}[\operatorname{E}[y_{ij} | \mu_j , \sigma]|\mu, \tau^2] +\operatorname{E}[\operatorname{Var}[y_{ij} | \mu_j , \sigma]|\mu, \tau^2] \\ &= \operatorname{Var}[\mu_j | \mu , \tau^2] + \operatorname{E}[\sigma^2] \\ &= \tau^2 + \operatorname{E}[\sigma^2]\end{align}\)

\(\begin{align}\operatorname{Var}[\bar y_{\cdot,j} | \mu , \tau^2] &= \operatorname{Var}[\operatorname{E}[\bar y_{\cdot,j} | \mu_j , \sigma]|\mu, \tau^2] +\operatorname{E}[\operatorname{Var}[\bar y_{\cdot,j} | \mu_j , \sigma]|\mu, \tau^2] \\ &= \operatorname{Var}[\mu_j | \mu , \tau^2] + \operatorname{E}[\sigma^2]/n_j \\ &= \tau^2 + \operatorname{E}[\sigma^2] / n_j\end{align}\)

\(\begin{align} \operatorname{Cov}[y_{i_1, j}, y_{i_2, j}| \mu, \tau^2] &= \operatorname{Cov}[\operatorname{E}[y_{i_1, j} | \theta_j, \sigma^2 ] \times \operatorname{E}[y_{i_2, j} | \theta_j, \sigma^2 ] |\mu, \tau^2 ] + \operatorname{E} [\operatorname{Cov(y_{i_1, j}, y_{i_2,j}|\theta_j , \sigma^2)}|\mu, \tau^2] \\ &= \operatorname{Cov}[\operatorname{E}[y_{i_1, j} | \theta_j, \sigma^2 ] \times \operatorname{E}[y_{i_2, j} | \theta_j, \sigma^2 ] |\mu, \tau^2 ] + 0 \\&= \operatorname{Cov}[\operatorname{E}[y_{i_1, j} | \theta_j, \sigma^2 ] \times \operatorname{E}[y_{i_2, j} | \theta_j, \sigma^2 ] |\mu, \tau^2 ] \\ &= \operatorname{Cov[\theta_j , \theta_j | \mu, \tau^2]} \\ &= \tau^2 \end{align}\)

d

Interpret \(p(\mu | \theta_1 , \cdots, \theta_m , \sigma^2, \tau^2, \boldsymbol y_1, \cdots, \boldsymbol y_m) = p(\mu | \theta_1, \cdots, \theta_m , \tau^2)\)

\(\theta_1, \cdots \theta_m, \tau^2\)이 주어지면 \(\mu\)는 나머지에 대해서 독립이다. 그래프를 그려보면 쉽게 보인다.

8.3

library(tidyverse)
school = list()
for(i in 1:8){
    url = paste0('http://www2.stat.duke.edu/~pdh10/FCBS/Exercises/school', as.character(i), '.dat')
    school[paste0('school', as.character(i))] = read.csv(url)
}
school_df <- data_frame(id = seq_along(school), school) %>% unnest %>% as.data.frame()
## Warning: `data_frame()` is deprecated, use `tibble()`.
## This warning is displayed once per session.
colnames(school_df) <- c('school_id', 'score')

modelString <- "
model{

## likelihood
for (i in 1:N){
y[i] ~ dnorm(mu_j[id[i]], invsigma2)
}

##hyperprior
mu ~ dnorm(mu0, 1/g0^2)
invtau2 ~ dgamma(a_t, b_t)
tau <- sqrt(pow(invtau2, -1))

##prior
for (j in 1:J){
mu_j[j] ~ dnorm(mu, invtau2)
}
invsigma2 ~ dgamma(a_g, b_g)
sigma <- sqrt(pow(invsigma2, -1))
}
"
y <- school_df %>% pull(score)
id <- school_df %>% pull(school_id)
N <- length(y)
J <- length(unique(id))

initsfunction <- function(chain){
    .RNG.seed <- c(1,2)[chain]
    .RNG.name <- c('base::Super-Duper',
                   'base::Wichmann-Hill')[chain]
    return(list(.RNG.seed=.RNG.seed,
                .RNG.name=.RNG.name))
}

the_data <- list('y'=y, 'id'=id, 'N'=N, 'J'=J,
                 'mu0'=7, 'g0'=sqrt(5),
                 'a_t'=1, 'b_t'=10,
                 'a_g'=1, 'b_g'=15)
library(runjags)
runjags.options(silent.runjags=TRUE, silent.jags=TRUE)
posterior <- run.jags(modelString,
                      n.chains = 1,
                      data = the_data,
                      monitor = c('mu', 'tau', 'mu_j', 'sigma'),
                      adapt = 1000,
                      burnin = 5000,
                      sample = 5000,
                      thin = 1,
                      inits = initsfunction)
plot(posterior)

summary(posterior)
